More than 900 people have recovered from COVID-19 in South Africa.  #DStv403 Angelique Coetzee from the South African Medical Association speaks to eNCA. JOHANNESBURG - The South Africa Medical Association (SAMA) is urging people to continue following precautionary measures. This as the number of recoveries from COVID-19 reach more than 900. Explainer: New amendments to the lockdown regulations The association's Angelique Coetzee says the country is still in a learning curve and that recoveries depend on your immune system and how well you look after yourself. The total number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in South Africa is 2, 783. The number of people who have died of coronavirus has risen to 50. Watch the full interview with the South Africa Medical Association's Angelique Coetzee in the video above.  For an updated number of cases, click here. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs. 